39:41.080 --> 39:46.080
I never loved anyone
the way I loved Annalise.

39:46.080 --> 39:48.620
I loved her even when
she didn't choose me.

39:48.620 --> 39:51.040
Wake up!
Alright, you wake up!

39:51.040 --> 39:52.920
Bonnie!

39:52.920 --> 39:55.120
Bonnie, wake up!
I need you!

39:55.120 --> 39:57.420
No!
You stay with me!

39:57.420 --> 39:58.880
Aah!

39:58.880 --> 40:00.540
You stay with me!

40:00.540 --> 40:02.000
Bonnie!

40:02.000 --> 40:05.420
Bonnie! Gah!
Oh, God!

40:05.420 --> 40:08.830
But those moments
when she did choose me?

40:08.830 --> 40:11.500
I would feel seen.

40:11.500 --> 40:14.420
I think we all seek
that person in our lives --

40:14.420 --> 40:17.120
someone who shows us
it's possible to survive

40:17.120 --> 40:19.580
whatever good or bad
is thrown at you.

40:21.790 --> 40:25.960
♪ If I let go,
would you hold on? ♪

40:25.960 --> 40:29.040
It's one of the thousand things
Annalise taught me.

40:29.040 --> 40:32.750
What feels like hell right now
is a gift later.

40:32.750 --> 40:36.540
♪ ...just say that we tried? ♪

40:36.540 --> 40:40.750
That's not to say
Annalise was easy to love.

40:40.750 --> 40:45.250
But then when you thought of
that young girl from Memphis,

40:45.250 --> 40:48.920
